cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing and specifically focuses on unsupervised abstractive sentence compression. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of a pretrained language model and gradient-based optimization, which suggests that it may also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks and autoencoders may also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the possibility of using image captioning as a future application, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
